{"timestamp":"2026-03-14T04:04:32.195Z","level":"WARN","message":"codex stderr","iteration":15,"chunk":"codex\nChanged files: [types.ts](c:/Users/ben.jones/source/repos/Ralph/RalphDex/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/src/ralph/types.ts), [stateManager.ts](c:/Users/ben.jones/source/repos/Ralph/RalphDex/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/src/ralph/stateManager.ts), [iterationEngine.ts](c:/Users/ben.jones/source/repos/Ralph/RalphDex/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/src/ralph/iterationEngine.ts), [stateManager.test.ts](c:/Users/ben.jones/source/repos/Ralph/RalphDex/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/test/stateManager.test.ts).\n\nI added optional `agentId` to `RalphIterationResult` and `RalphRunRecord`, introduced `DEFAULT_RALPH_AGENT_ID = 'default'`, and threaded that sentinel through iteration creation, run-record creation, and state normalization. Existing state files without `agentId` now load as `default` without migration, and run-to-iteration backfill keeps the same value.\n\nValidation: `cd ralph-codex-vscode-starter && npm run compile` passed.\n\nAssumptions/blockers: I assumed the single-agent sentinel should be the literal `'default'` and that this task only required the state/result schema and persistence path, not yet wiring a distinct multi-agent source into iteration execution. No blocker.\n\nKnown limitations/follow-up: the current execution path still emits the sentinel for all CLI runs; a later multi-agent task should replace that with the real claim `agentId` at claim/acquire time so the provenance join is fully live.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"selectedTaskId\": \"T24.3.1\",\n  \"requestedStatus\": \"done\",\n  \"progressNote\": \"Added optional agentId to RalphIterationResult and RalphRunRecord, defaulted legacy/missing records to the 'default' sentinel in state normalization, and persisted the sentinel on newly created single-agent iteration/run records. Compile passed.\",\n  \"validationRan\": \"cd ralph-codex-vscode-starter && npm run compile\"\n}\n```\n"}
